<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-set_descrp" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Description</title>

  <p> 
    Sets are represented by three different forms: 
    <ol>
      <li>
        Description or Statement Form: <m> 2, 4, 6, 8, \ldots = \{\text{even numbers} \}</m> by using statement.
        <m> a, e, i, o, u = \{\text{vowels of english alphabet} \}</m>.
       </li>
      <li>
       Roster or Tabular Form: <m>\{ a,e,i,o,u\}</m> by using commas.
      </li>
      <li>
        Set-Builder or Rule Form: <m>\{ x: x \text{ is a vowel} \}</m> or  <m>\{ x| x \text{ is a vowel} \}</m>  by using its property.
       
      </li>
    </ol> 
  </p>
  <p>
    See examples in <xref ref="sec_set-exampleA"/>.
  </p>




</section>